                            <comment id="15438641" author="romain.manni-bucau" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2016 08:12:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;note that it is not a trivial change since API JsonValue (booleans and null) are NOT serializable. This imply you need to compare using readValue.equals(JsonValue.XXX) to ensure the application still works.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15438762" author="struberg" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2016 10:17:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wont work -&amp;gt; -1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Problem is that blabla == JsonValue.TRUE wont work anymore. That totally defeats the purpose of JsonValue.TRUE, FALSE and NULL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need a spec change for that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15438765" author="struberg" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2016 10:19:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;see &lt;a href=&quot;https://java.net/jira/browse/JSON_PROCESSING_SPEC-73&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://java.net/jira/browse/JSON_PROCESSING_SPEC-73&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15439347" author="romain.manni-bucau" created="Fri, 26 Aug 2016 16:23:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated the commit:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;JsonObject and JsonArray are serializable (they are serialized as String then deserialized through a JsonReader)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;JsonString and JsonNumber are serializable directly&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;JsonValue.&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;TRUE|FALSE|NULL&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; are not serializable (belongs to the API) directly (but in an Object or Array no problem)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15994425" author="struberg" created="Wed, 3 May 2017 07:48:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;shipped with Johnzon-1.0.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
